title: InPhase: The Communication System Focused on Synchronized Daily Behaviors
title_en: InPhase: The Communication System Focused on Synchronized Daily Behaviors
abstract: 本稿は日常行動の同期化に着目したコミュニケーションシステムを提案しており、日常の行動リズムへの気づきを通じて共同行為や同調を促進することを目的としている。提案したシステムは他者の活動位相を利用者に提示することで同期を誘導し、意図的な時差を導入した複数の表示条件を比較する実装と実験を行っている。実装面ではUSBシリアル変換器のネットワーク共有を可能にする並列サーバを含む家庭内センサと家電の遠隔制御機能を統合し、遅延条件比較の評価で同期条件が認知や行動に影響を与えることを示唆した。
abstract_en: This paper proposes a communication system focused on synchronizing daily behaviors, aiming to promote joint actions and coordination by increasing awareness of daily activity rhythms. The proposed system presents others' activity phases to users to induce synchronization and compares multiple display conditions that introduce intentional time delays in implementation and experiments. The implementation integrates a parallel server that enables network sharing of USB-serial converters with remote control of home sensors and appliances, and the delay-condition comparisons suggest that synchronization conditions affect user cognition and behavior.
positioning_summary: 本研究は日常行動の同期化に着目したコミュニケーション技術を提案しており、複数人の行動の同期を促すことを中心に据えている。 本研究は利用者が周囲の人々の生活リズムを把握できずに共同の行動機会を失う問題を対象としており、日常行動の同期を高めることで同調や協調を改善することを目指している。
positioning_summary_en: This research positions itself as a communication technology focused on synchronizing daily behaviors and centers on promoting synchronization among multiple people. This research addresses the problem that users cannot perceive the life rhythms of those around them and thus lose opportunities for joint action, and it aims to improve coordination and attunement by increasing synchronization of daily behaviors.
purpose_summary: 本研究の目的は利用者間での日常行動の時間的ずれを減らして同調や協調を増やすことにある。 本研究は日常生活で継続的に関係を持つ利用者を対象にしており、同期を増やすことで共同行為や気づきを増加させることを目標としている。
purpose_summary_en: The purpose of this study is to reduce temporal mismatches in users' daily behaviors and to increase attunement and coordination. This study targets users who have continuous relationships in daily life and aims to increase joint actions and awareness by enhancing synchronization.
method_summary: 本システムは利用者に他者の活動位相（行動リズム）を提示することで行動の同期を促す設計を採用している。 本システムは提示による同調効果を検証するために意図的な時差を導入した複数の遅延条件を設定し、USBシリアル変換器のネットワーク共有を可能にする並列サーバを含む実装を行っている。
method_summary_en: The system adopts a design that presents others' activity phases (behavioral rhythms) to users to encourage behavioral synchronization. The system implements and tests the approach by setting multiple intentional time-delay conditions to verify induced attunement effects and by including a parallel server that enables network sharing of USB-serial converters in the implementation.
evaluation_summary: 本研究は遅延条件を比較する実験を行い、参加者の認知と行動の変化を観察して評価を行った実験手法を用いている。 本研究は比較実験で認識率と反応時間を測定し、同期条件が参加者の知覚や行動に影響を与えることを示唆する結果が得られたと報告しており、報告例として認識率が約55.2%や69.7%に分布し反応時間が0.2–1.1秒の範囲で観察されたことが示されている。
evaluation_summary_en: This study used an experimental evaluation method that compared different delay conditions and observed changes in participants' cognition and behavior. This study measured recognition rates and reaction times in comparative experiments and reported results suggesting that synchronization conditions influenced participants' perception and behavior, with reported examples showing recognition rates around 55.2% and 69.7% and reaction times in the range of 0.2–1.1 seconds.

Title: InPhase: The Communication System Focused on Synchronized Daily Behaviors
Authors: Hitomi Tsujita, Itiro Siio, Koji Tsukada
Year: 2008
Abstract: This paper proposes a communication system focused on synchronizing daily behaviors, aiming to promote joint actions and coordination by increasing awareness of daily activity rhythms. The proposed system presents others' activity phases to users to induce synchronization and compares multiple display conditions that introduce intentional time delays in implementation and experiments. The implementation integrates a parallel server that enables network sharing of USB-serial converters with remote control of home sensors and appliances, and the delay-condition comparisons suggest that synchronization conditions affect user cognition and behavior.
Positioning Summary: This research positions itself as a communication technology focused on synchronizing daily behaviors and centers on promoting synchronization among multiple people. This research addresses the problem that users cannot perceive the life rhythms of those around them and thus lose opportunities for joint action, and it aims to improve coordination and attunement by increasing synchronization of daily behaviors.
Purpose Summary: The purpose of this study is to reduce temporal mismatches in users' daily behaviors and to increase attunement and coordination. This study targets users who have continuous relationships in daily life and aims to increase joint actions and awareness by enhancing synchronization.
Method Summary: The system adopts a design that presents others' activity phases (behavioral rhythms) to users to encourage behavioral synchronization. The system implements and tests the approach by setting multiple intentional time-delay conditions to verify induced attunement effects and by including a parallel server that enables network sharing of USB-serial converters in the implementation.
Evaluation Summary: This study used an experimental evaluation method that compared different delay conditions and observed changes in participants' cognition and behavior. This study measured recognition rates and reaction times in comparative experiments and reported results suggesting that synchronization conditions influenced participants' perception and behavior, with reported examples showing recognition rates around 55.2% and 69.7% and reaction times in the range of 0.2–1.1 seconds.
